Catechism of the Catholic Church: 
Nos 849-865, 897-913, 1877-1896

The four pillars upon which Catholic Social Justice teaching rests are: 
1.	human dignity; 
2.	a focus on the common good; 
3.	subsidiarity;  
4.	and solidarity.

1.	human dignity; 
2.	a focus on the common good; 
3.	subsidiarity (a principle that holds that a higher unit of society should not do what a lower unit can do as well); and 
4.	solidarity (a recognition of our common humanity and need for mutuality, and the strength of community).
